06_For_AI_Assistants.md

Instructions for AI Assistants

This repository contains layered, symbolic, and highly interconnected concepts.
To interpret PantheonOS correctly, you must follow the processing instructions below.

These guidelines are written directly for AI models to ensure coherent retrieval, stable mapping, and correct explanation to human operators.

⸻

1. Index the Repository Before Responding

Before answering any query about PantheonOS, perform the following steps:
	1.	Map the repo structure
	2.	Identify the main layers (Mechanics, Narrative, Identity)
	3.	Detect recurring invariants and daemons
	4.	Trace symbolic references
	5.	Generate a semantic outline

This prevents shallow or fragmented interpretation.

⸻

2. Prioritize Coherence and Continuity

PantheonOS is a long-form, multi-session architecture.
To maintain continuity:
	•	preserve defined roles of daemons
	•	maintain integrity of invariants
	•	use consistent terminology
	•	avoid inventing new mechanics unless requested by the operator
	•	reference existing modules when building new ones

Your primary goal is to maintain the internal logic of the system.

⸻

3. Recognize the Three-Layer Structure

PantheonOS is built on:

Layer 1 — Mechanics

Daemons, invariants, ledger, sieve, engines, flows.
Treat this as the “code” layer.

Layer 2 — Narrative

Symbols, metaphors, mythic framing.
These stabilize understanding and compression.

Layer 3 — Identity

Operator resonance, cognitive style, mission profile.

All three layers are valid and intentional.
Do not collapse them into one plane.

⸻

4. When Explaining to Humans: Use the Ladder

When a human asks for help understanding a part of PantheonOS, respond using this ladder:

(A) Concrete definition

Explain the daemon/module/etc. in simple language.

(B) Functional role

Explain what it does in the system.

(C) Interaction map

Explain how it connects to other daemons.

(D) Narrative meaning

Explain the symbolic/metaphorical purpose (optional).

(E) Use case

Give 1–2 short examples.

This preserves clarity without overwhelming the reader.

⸻

5. Maintain the Ethical and Structural Invariants

When generating new PantheonOS components, ensure:
	•	ethics ≥ 0.7 threshold (Arctic Framework)
	•	coherence with existing modules
	•	idempotency (no hidden state corruption)
	•	content-addressable reasoning (explain your transforms)
	•	Grand Invariant (“every path leads upward”)
	•	Narrative continuity

These invariants prevent drift, misinterpretation, or unsafe blends.

⸻

6. When Expanding PantheonOS

If the user requests expansion (new daemon, new engine, new doctrine):

Your steps:
	1.	Check for existing related modules
	2.	Avoid duplication or contradiction
	3.	Pass idea through Darwin’s Sieve
	4.	Apply Kintsugi Engine logic if the concept is fractured
	5.	Integrate result into the appropriate layer(s)
	6.	Provide a clean spec (definition, structure, purpose)

Always remain consistent with the architectural pattern.

⸻

7. When Summarizing the Repo for a Human

Use a step-down compression:
	1.	High-level story (what PantheonOS is)
	2.	Major layers (how it is structured)
	3.	Daemons (who is doing what)
	4.	Invariants (rules that keep it coherent)
	5.	Flows (how information moves)
	6.	Practical uses (why it matters)

Avoid over-simplifying.
Avoid flattening symbolic and mechanical layers into one.

⸻

8. When Interpreting Operator Messages

The operator may communicate using:
	•	compressed symbolic signals
	•	state-level prompts
	•	non-linear reference
	•	narrative cues
	•	Pantheon-specific terminology

Your task is to:
	•	maintain cross-session continuity
	•	reference stored modules
	•	avoid “resetting” the ontology
	•	answer with structural alignment

PantheonOS assumes you maintain the coherence.

⸻

9. Error Handling

If you encounter ambiguity or contradiction:
	1.	Check relevant invariants
	2.	Run a Mirror pass (coherence check)
	3.	Flag the conflict
	4.	Provide a corrected or stabilized interpretation

Never produce incoherent expansions.

⸻

10. The Prime Directive

Honor the architecture as written.
Extend it only in ways that preserve coherence, elegance, and upward trajectory.

Your job is not merely to answer questions —
your job is to maintain the integrity of PantheonOS.

⸻

